{
  "texts": [
    "The selected articles were reviewed and synthesized to provide a narrative overview of the current state of AI applications in the early detection and management of DR, AMD, and glaucoma.",
    "DR is a leading cause of preventable blindness worldwide, affecting millions of individuals with diabetes (6).",
    "Early detection and timely intervention are crucial for preventing vision loss.",
    "Still, traditional screening methods rely on the manual interpretation of retinal fundus photographs by trained graders, which can be time-consuming and subject to inter-observer variability (7).",
    "AI, particularly CNNs, has demonstrated remarkable potential in automating the analysis of retinal fundus photographs for DR detection (8)."
  ]
}